%N A279228 Number of unit steps that are shared by the smallest and largest Dyck path of the symmetric representation of sigma(n).
%C A279228 a(n) is also the number of unit steps that are shared by the largest Dyck path of the symmetric representation of sigma(n) and the largest Dyck path of the symmetric representation of sigma(n-1), in a quadrant of the square grid.
%C A279228 For more information about the Dyck paths of the symmetric representation of sigma(n) see A237593.
%F A279228 a(n) = 2*n - A244363(n) = 2*(n - A244361(n)).
%F A279228 a(n) = A008586(n) - A348705(n). - _Omar E. Pol_, Dec 13 2021
